{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38427f4b-acfc-48dd-928c-e9d918396318","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\nHere are the main tools for analyzing `.dmp` files from .NET apps:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the REPL:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n### `lldb` + SOS (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso`, etc.\n\n### Visual Studio / WinDbg (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` file directly in Visual Studio or WinDbg for a full debugging experience.\n\n---\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp`\n2. Type `pe` to print the exception that caused the crash\n3. Type `clrstack` to see the stack trace\n4. If multi-threaded, use `threads` then `setthread <id>` + `clrstack`\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start analyzing the file? If so, share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8bdc57b7-f71e-487a-8923-efb3f0a96b81","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill doesn't apply here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":466,"requestId":"A0C0:71616:CF4257:100C7AF:6A0137F3"},"id":"bde5824a-1fe4-4856-947b-1ac0be8002f0","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:59:27.706Z","parentId":"f3d689ea-882e-40e1-981c-e06460e84aca"}
